# Testing Rules

## Responsibility

Prove Code matches Specifications.

## Practice

- Map tests to Spec IDs wherever practical
- Prefer regression tests for production bugs
- Keep cross-cutting tests in `/tests`; unit tests near code
- Treat flaky tests as defects

## Forbidden

- “Tests later” for Must-priority Specs at release time
- Asserting implementation details that Specs do not require
- Selecting a new test framework without Architecture/ADR

## Definition of verified

A change is verified when acceptance criteria in the Spec are covered by automated and/or documented manual checks.
